news.title: Bank of Spain sees small overvaluation in real estate prices
news.para: Earlier this month, national statistics institute INE said its property price index rose 4.2% in the third quarter, the biggest increase since the same quarter of 2019, following a 3.3% rise in Q2.

news.title: Hewlett Packard takes 1.8 lakh sq ft office space on lease in Chennai
news.para: HP will use the new facility to house around 1800 employees. “The office space was coming up Prestige Metropolitan and signed at Rs 75 per sqft. The lease is for 15 years,” said people aware of the deal.

news.title: RLDA to monetise New Jalpaiguri Barrack colony
news.para: The bid carries a reserve price of Rs 26.7 crore for the area of 16,222 Sqm to be leased out for 99 years. The online pre-bid meeting was held where prominent national and local level developers participated. The last date of e-bid submission is January 28, 2022.

news.title: Centre approves construction of 1.07 lakh houses in five states under PMAY-U
news.para: The total investment under the mission is Rs 7.52 lakh crore, with central assistance of Rs 1.85 lakh crore. So far, central assistance amounting to Rs 1.14 lakh crore has already been released.

news.title: Nearly 5 lakh Bengaluru properties have not paid tax
news.para: According to data tabled during the question hour in the legislative council, over 18.5 lakh properties in the city fall under tax purview of the Palike and are divided into different categories.

news.title: Aurangabad's climate action plan to come up by 2023
news.para: ​​The Aurangabad Municipal Corporation (AMC) and the Aurangabad Smart City Development Corporation (ASCDCL) have hired World Resources Institute, India (WRI) to prepare the city's climate action plan.

news.title: Real estate sector lists demands ahead of Vibrant Gujarat Global Summit
news.para: The major one is a 50% cut in stamp duty and registration fees, which represents a sizable chunk of government revenue.

news.title: GIS-based master plan for nine cities in Bihar to be made soon
news.para: The nine cities have been divided into three groups with Araria, Forbesganj and Khagaria falling in the first group, Lakhisarai, Jamui and Bhahua in the second group and Sheohar, Sitamarhi and Madhubani in the third group.

news.title: Maharashtra: Board for old buildings in suburbs likely
news.para: The issue of old and dilapidated buildings was raised through a calling attention motion by legislators Bhai Jagtap, Wajahat Mirza and others.

news.title: Engineers will now face action if building plans are violated in Tamil Nadu
news.para: The government is working on the quantum of penalty and punishment for registered professionals, ahead of launching the initiative aimed at averting the delay in issuing the planning permits.

news.title: Nashik: EV charging stations must for all new buildings with 25+ flats
news.para: NMC commissioner Kailas Jadhav said he has already passed an order and directed the town planning department to not approve building plan proposals if they do not have provisions for EV charging stations.

news.title: DHFL case: Yes Bank's former business head gets bail
news.para: ​​Anand's bail plea was allowed by special judge for CBI cases S U Wadgaonkar. The detailed order was not available yet. The bank's co-founder Rana Kapoor and his family are co-accused in the case.

news.title: Delhi court takes cognisance of charge sheet against Unitech promoters
news.para: "Considering the material available on record, I take cognisance for the commission of offence punishable under section 3 and 4 (money laundering) of Prevention of Money Laundering Act (PMLA). Let accused persons be summoned for next date of hearing," the judge said.

news.title: Essar Steel Metal Trading buys luxury duplex in Mumbai's Worli for Rs 42 crore
news.para: The deal values the luxury pad at more than Rs 1.44 lakh per sq ft, making it one of the costliest apartment transactions in the country. The duplex spread over 3,638 sq ft carpet area is on the 21st and 22nd floor of the sea-facing building on Dr. Annie Besant Road.

news.title: Debenture holders oppose Adani Realty's bid for Radius Estates
news.para: ICICI Pru AMC and Beacon Trusteeship, who hold debentures of Radius, have approached NCLT to stop voting on Adani’s bid.
